value.value: A vegetable whose foliage, or foliage-bearing stalks, are the chief edible part.
A variant of lymphomatoid papulosis characterized by an epidermotropic infiltrate composed of small atypical cerebriform-like lymphocytes.
A variant of lymphomatoid papulosis characterized clinically by regressing skin papules, and morphologically by features resembling anaplastic large cell lymphoma.
The pod-enclosed seed of various leguminous herbs as well as other vegetable seeds or fruits that resemble true beans.

A leafy green vegetable and a member of the Gemmifera group of cabbages that contains high amounts of phytochemicals, with potential chemopreventive activity. Brussels sprouts contain high amounts of the glycosinolate glucobrassicin. Upon consumption of Brussels sprouts, the phytochemicals in the vegetable, and some of their metabolites, are able to induce the expression of various hepatic cytochrome P450 monooxygenases, scavenge free radicals and may inhibit the activation of various signal transduction pathways.

The sodium salt form of oxacillin, a semisynthetic penicillinase-resistant and acid-stable penicillin with an antimicrobial activity. Oxacillin binds to penicillin-binding proteins in the bacterial cell wall, thereby blocking the synthesis of peptidoglycan, a critical component of the bacterial cell wall. This leads to inhibition of cell growth and causes cell lysis.

label.value: Anaplastic Large Cell Lymphoma, Lymphomatoid Papulosis-Like Histology

value.value: An anaplastic large cell lymphoma characterized by the presence of histopathologic features reminiscent of lymphomatoid papulosis. These features include the presence of Hodgkin-like cells in a background of acute and chronic inflammation.
A person who manages a computer, a network or specific software components and has rights to perform all operations.
